  "prompt": "How did you get into IIM?",
  "response": "To gain admission to an Indian Institute of Management (IIM), candidates typically follow a structured process, usually involving the following steps:\n\n1. **Undergraduate Education**: Most candidates complete a bachelor's degree in any discipline from a recognized university.\n\n2. **Preparing for the CAT Exam**: Prospective students prepare for the Common Admission Test (CAT), which is the primary entrance exam for IIMs. This exam tests quantitative ability, verbal ability, reading comprehension, and logical reasoning.\n\n3. **Taking the CAT Exam**: Candidates register for and take the CAT, usually conducted once a year.\n\n4. **Shortlisting for Interviews**: Based on CAT scores, candidates are shortlisted for the next stage, which may include a Written Ability Test (WAT) and a Personal Interview (PI).\n\n5. **Interviews and Evaluations**: Candidates participate in interviews, and their overall profiles are evaluated, including academic records, work experience, and extracurricular activities.\n\n6. **Final Selection**: After interviews and evaluations, candidates receive admission offers based on their overall performance.\n\n7. **Joining the Program**: Accepted candidates complete the enrollment process and begin their studies.\n\nEach IIM may have specific eligibility criteria and processes, so it\u2019s always good to check the official website for detailed information.",
